00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:09,520
Eight years ago?

179
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,640
You don't know?

180
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:17,260
How about you tell Mr. Luo what happened eight years ago?

181
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,540
8 years ago, Mu Dai was 15.

182
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:26,820
 Back then,   I adopted her and have raised her for a dozen years. 

183
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,320
 She was adorable. 

184
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,940
 She was outgoing too. 

185
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,400
 Mu Dai. 

186
00:16:41,326 --> 00:16:43,660
 - It's for you. 
 - Thanks. Let's go. 

187
00:16:43,660 --> 00:16:45,220
 I was looking for you. 

188
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:46,440
 Where are we going? 

189
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:50,360
 In her class, she had a close friend named Shen Wen. 

190
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:55,400
They stuck together as if they were hand in glove.

191
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,760
But later...

192
00:17:00,718 --> 00:17:02,640
Something happened.

193
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:05,760
After school, they usually went to a tutoring center.

194
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:11,240
But one night, they didn't come home even when it was 11 p.m.

195
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,120
Their phones were disconnected.

196
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:18,200
We talked to their tutor, only to know they had skipped class.

197
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:21,500
 Wen Wen's mother and I looked everywhere, street by street. 

198
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,800
 - Wen Wen! 
 - We ended up at an alleyway. 

199
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:25,560
 Mu Dai! 

200
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,680
 - Wen Wen! 
 - Where are they? 

201
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,680
 It's Mu Dai's phone. 

202
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:46,920
 - Where are they? 
 - Don't worry. 

203
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:49,020
 Wen Wen! 

204
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,800
 Wen Wen! 

205
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:54,520
 That was a deserted construction site. 

206
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:56,780
We went in there.

207
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,960
We saw...

208
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:03,760
Mu Dai had fallen downstairs.

209
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:06,307
The back of her head was bleeding.

210
00:18:06,307 --> 00:18:08,067
Then...

211
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:11,760
We found Wen Wen in the building.

212
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,560
She...

213
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:16,320
She was dead.

214
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,860
Mu Dai was in a coma for several days.

215
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:22,720
When she woke up, she told us the story.

216
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,840
That night,

217
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:28,660
they skipped class for a movie.

218
00:18:29,601 --> 00:18:34,500
But on their way, they met some rogues.

219
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:37,200
That's why she had a problem.

220
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,840
Those rogues were caught soon and sentenced.

221
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,800
But Shen Wen's parents lost their daughter.

222
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:46,980
They had no way to let the pain out.

223
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:51,120
So, they blamed everything on Mu Dai.

224
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,780
Wen Wen was a top student in her class.

225
00:18:53,780 --> 00:18:55,580
She was always obedient.

226
00:18:55,580 --> 00:19:00,300
Her parents insisted Mu Dai nudged her into skipping class.

227
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:04,440
 If you hadn't taken her out, she wouldn't have been killed! 

228
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:08,340
And some guys said Wen Wen could have run away.

229
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:10,540
She returned to save Mu Dai.

230
00:19:10,540 --> 00:19:11,660
 Kneel before my sister! 

231
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:12,800
 - Kneel! 
 - Sinner! 

232
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,740
 - Kneel! 
 - Kneel now! 

233
00:19:14,740 --> 00:19:15,780
 - Stop hassling her. 
 - Sinner. 

234
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:19,440
 After that, instead of blaming those rogues, 

235
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:21,960
 they blamed Mu Dai. 

236
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,880
 - Pay with your life! 
 - Don't hit her. 

237
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,080
 - Die! 
 - Don't. 

238
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:26,980
 - Don't do this. 
 - How unfair! 

239
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:28,400
 Don't hit her. Please don't. 

240
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,600
 Why is my daughter dead alone? 

241
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:34,240
 Mu Dai hit her head and had little memory of that. 

242
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:37,520
 When Shen Wen's family questioned her, she couldn't explain anything. 

243
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:38,840
They took her silence as a yes.

244
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:42,000
As the only person who could protect her,

245
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,480
didn't you defend her?

246
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:45,720
Defend her? How?

247
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,200
Their child was killed.

248
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:50,000
Mu Dai survived, after all.

249
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,960
I asked Mu Dai to bear with it. Then, it would be over.

250
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,912
But that day...

251
00:19:54,912 --> 00:19:56,460
 Mu Dai. 

252
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,360
 Mu Dai. It's okay now. 

253
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:01,160
 It's okay. 

254
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,600
 Mu Dai, who did this? 

255
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,000
 Who? 

256
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:17,400
 Who did this? They went too far! 

257
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,400
 Mu Dai. 

258
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,460
 Auntie Hong. 

259
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,780
 It's my fault. 

260
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,800
 Auntie Hong. 

261
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:41,280
 I should have died. 

262
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:43,320
 Don't say that. 

263
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,460
 It's okay, Mu Dai. 

264
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,620
 You have me. 

265
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:50,820
 I'll protect you. 

266
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:57,480
Only then did I realize

267
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:01,880
Mu Dai had a mental problem.

268
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:04,380
Silence grew in her,

269
00:21:06,020 --> 00:21:08,460
and she barely talked to anyone.

270
00:21:08,460 --> 00:21:11,440
She remained sleepless.

271
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:14,180
I couldn't let this continue.

272
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:17,040
So, we moved away.

273
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:20,320
Then, she began to see doctors.

274
